The paper proposes a novel method for interlinking datasets in the Linked Data Cloud using machine learning techniques. This involves matching instances between a source and target dataset without prior knowledge of the data, domain or schema of these datasets. This problem falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with data management and integration, which is a key area of research in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for matching instances between datasets. Finally, the paper deals with semantic integration (cs.SI) of datasets, which is a key area of research in the Semantic Web community.
